    dc:date "2020" ;
    dc:title "Disentangling vines: a study of morphological crypsis and genetic divergence in vine snakes (Squamata: Colubridae: Ahaetulla) with the description of five new species from Peninsular India" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423555>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423530>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423559> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423555>
    dc:description "FIGURE 15. Images of Ahaetulla malabarica sp. nov. Images of Holotype BNHS 3586 (CESS090). (a) Head lateral, (b) Head dorsal, (c) Ventral section, (d–f) Everted Hemipenis. Whole specimen (CESS090). Head lateral images of different colour morphs (live), (g) CESS090 from Brahmagiri, (h) CESS144 from Siruvani, (i) CESS143 from Poochipara, (j) CESS090 from Brahmagiri. Image of a live, uncollected individual, (k) Whole animal from Brahmagiri Hills (Images a & b; d & e to scale, other images not to scale)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4423555/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423530>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Ahaetulla lineages in Peninsular India and Sri Lanka showing side-by-side comparison of their superficial head morphology and maxillary dentition. (From the top) (a) Ahaetulla farnsworthi sp. nov. (b) A. isabellina comb. nov. (c) A. malabarica sp. nov. (d) A. borealis sp. nov. (e) A. nasuta (f) A. oxyrhyncha comb. nov. (g) A. sahyadrensis nom. nov. (h) A. travancorica sp. nov. (i) A. dispar & A. travancorica sp. nov. (j) A. perroteti (1) Ahaetulla farnsworthi sp. nov. (2) A. isabellina comb. nov. (3) A. malabarica sp. nov. (4) A. borealis sp. nov. (5) A. nasuta (6) A. oxyrhyncha comb. nov. (7) A. pulverulenta (8) A. sahyadrensis nom. nov. (9) A. dispar (10) A. travancorica sp. nov. (11) A. perroteti." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4423530/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4423559>
    dc:description "FIGURE 16. Habitat of Ahaetulla malabarica sp. nov. in Brahmagiri Hills, Central Western Ghats (borders Kodagu district, Karnataka State and Waynad district, Kerala State, India) showing semi-evergreen and evergreen forest vegetation types." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4423559/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

